 Guests had the opportunity to enjoy an informative meeting during the Röhlig-Grindrod’s presentation at the Kruger Lowveld Chamber of Business and Tourism networking breakfast.    It was held on Wednesday at Nou’s Toeka. ALSO READ:Businesswomen get inspired to network Röhlig-Grindrod is a formidable player and trusted name in the logistics industry worldwide.  The talk was aimed at empowering existing and potential exporters and importers as well as people who cannot avoid the pain of logistics in their daily business.   ALSO READ: Tony Wake inspire locals during meet-greet-event They had the opportunity to get up to date with the new Customs Control Bill and Preferred Trader programme, cash flow management, how to prevent and resolve customs stops, guide through a customs compliance audit, duty increases, and reduction or rebates applications.